item.name: MySQL status
item.description:
It requires user parameter mysql.ping, which is defined in userparameter_mysql.conf.
0 - MySQL server is down 1 - MySQL server is up

item.name: MySQL aborted clients
item.description: The number of connections that were aborted because the client died without closing the connection properly

item.name: MySQL aborted connects
item.description: The number of failed attempts to connect to the MySQL server. As of MySQL 5.7.3, Aborted_connects is not visible in the embedded server because for that server it is not updated and is not meaningful.

item.name: MySQL bytes received per second
item.description:
The number of bytes received from all clients.
It requires user parameter mysql.status[*], which is defined in userparameter_mysql.conf.

item.name: MySQL bytes sent per second
item.description:
The number of bytes sent to all clients.
It requires user parameter mysql.status[*], which is defined in userparameter_mysql.conf.
